  abstract={Aiming at the limitations of traditional clutter suppression algorithms, which cannot achieve radar multipath signal suppression under a single receiving antenna and suffer from high interference when using 5G base stations to detect low-slow-small (LSS) targets, this study proposes a Multipath Clutter Suppression Algorithm Based on Single-Channel Environment Parameter Sensing (MCSEPS) for 5G base stations. The algorithm aims to suppress interfering signals through a single-channel configuration, thereby mitigating the impact of multipath clutter causing false targets when radar detects LSS drones. Algorithm process is as follows: First, set the search range for the received signal delay. Then, establish a signal amplitude estimation model to solve for direct wave signal parameters. After suppressing the direct wave, solve for multipath parameters again based on the set search range, filter out false multipath signals according to a threshold, and finally reconstruct multipath clutter using the recorded multipath parameters to complete the suppression of interfering signals. Experimental simulations show that the proposed method can effectively suppress multipath clutter under a single-channel configuration, with relatively low computational complexity, significantly reducing the impact of multipath clutter on radar target detection.},
